Very trendy and hipster. Not that I discount for that but it seemed like function took a back seat to form. During our stay a waitress dropped a plate while serving. Not her fault at all, ceramic slides on ceramic very easily, poor design on plating. As for my meal, I got a fried egg. It was cooked and served in a cast iron skillet. Bad choice in plating again. The cast iron retained so much heat that by the time I was able to eat the hot egg is was over cooked and rubbery. This is basic. Any cook should be able to cook and deliver an egg. And at $12 I expect it to be perfect.

Overpriced and not that good. Service was poor at the end of the day. I could not dress my coffee my self, they HAD to do it... too much milk, no half and half... tepid. Got a chocolate chip cookie, very little chocolate flavor, way too much crumble. Just shattered as you broke a piece off.
First visit today, charming and delicious, will definitely come back next year.

Go for the food, but definitely not for this particular store location. I went for brunch when the restaurant was nearly empty and received extremely poor customer service. I had to ask Michael (the waiter) to clean up the table before serving my food (as if it wasn't obvious). Later on when I ordered a cappuccino, I had to ask him to bring a spoon. Basically I was the one who was anticipating everything! Then when the bill came, he had included a pain au chocolat while I had actually ordered a blueberry muffin. He claimed it was the same price anyway until I pointed out to him the price difference of $1.50. He said nothing and updated my bill. I also felt uncomfortable when the waiter left with my credit card, went to another part of the restaurant from which I could not see him, and only came back a couple of minutes after. Most businesses bring a machine and/or complete the transaction in front of the customer, not the way that guy did at all. Awesome food, but quite miserable service unfortunately. Try the Union Station location instead, they are much better at what they do.

It was such a kind gesture, and we were incredibly thankful. We had such a lovely experience here, and we’re sure you’ll have the same!

Went to the counter and waited a little while for service.  Ordered a coffee black and received it in a take out cup.  I came in looking for a place to sit and drink some coffee but being my first time I didn't understand how the shop worked.  I took a seat and began nursing my coffee.  As more people entered I soon realized the establishment is more like a kind of sit down cafe with service rather than something like a starbucks or a panera.  The staff was very attentive to the other customers and hard working.  They however did not engage with me.  I am not sure if it was because they did not want to make me feel like they were pressuring me to hurry or anything like that.  I enjoyed the coffee, the atmosphere and the shop had a nice bathroom. I would not have objected to a "how is the coffee or would you like a glass of water" etc.  But I also appreciate the discretion to give a customer their peace.  I'd have given a tip but I did not really receive any service or even a "have a good day or come again" on the way out so I will instead give the staff the benefit of the doubt as to whther they just thought I was a homeless guy or something.  In the future I hope they will ask someone ordering if they would like the item for here or to go to avoid confusion for first timers like myself.

Headline: Good food, OK service  Atmosphere: This is just like any other place in this large chain, but the difference is they do have some outdoor seating that is really nice in this part of town. There is usually some shade and a nice summer breeze between 8:00 - 9:00 AM.  Food: The food is good and fresh. The portions are a little on the smaller size, but the flavor makes up for it.  Service: was OK. I was the only person sitting outside and there was only one server, and I only saw him a couple of times. I was the only person sitting outside so I can see how he could be distracted by everyone inside, but management should really have more staff especially for breakfast. This is where this place loses a star.  Overall: worth trying, especially if you sit outside and enjoy morning summer breeze.
